## Code Review: PR #617 — Verdict: REQUEST_CHANGES

**3 files reviewed** | **3 HIGH findings, 1 LOW**

### Findings

**Finding 1 — Missing `aria-expanded` on collapsible section buttons** (HIGH, accessibility)
`Sidebar.tsx:1147` — The `<button>` elements that replaced `<h2>` headers for section collapse have no `aria-expanded` attribute. Screen readers can't announce expanded/collapsed state. Fix: add `aria-expanded={!collapsedSections.has(group.type)}` to the button.

**Finding 2 — FAB type menu bottom items overlap with FAB button** (HIGH, visual bug)
`MobileFAB.tsx:93,112` — Both the type-select menu container and the FAB button are anchored at `fixed bottom-20 right-4 z-40`. With 4 menu items (~176px stacked height), the last 1–2 items ("Remember person", part of "Capture idea") are rendered behind the FAB button (which sits later in the DOM at the same z-index). The "Remember person" option may be unclickable. Fix: change the menu container to `bottom-36` to clear the FAB.

**Finding 3 — Screenshot tests not updated** (HIGH, CLAUDE.md violation)
CLAUDE.md explicitly requires running `test:screenshots:update` and visually inspecting PNGs when UI changes are made. This PR adds visible UI elements (collapsible headers, inline quick-add forms, MobileFAB) but no screenshots were committed.

**Finding 4 — `singularize` defined inside component body** (LOW, quality)
`Sidebar.tsx:503` — Pure function redefined every render. Should be hoisted to module scope.

### Positive
Error handling, error-state clearing, Escape key handling, store subscription patterns, and `person` type alignment are all done correctly.
